issues.description: The Virtual Connect domain has a status of warning or minor.
issues.recommendation: Review the status and resolve the issue causing the domain error status if necessary.

issues.description: The boot mode in profile "Profile_2" is configured as Auto and some PXE, FC, iSCSI, and FCoE connections are not configured to boot BIOS.
issues.recommendation: Configure all PXE, FC, iSCSI, and FCoE connections to boot from BIOS, or change the boot mode to something other than Auto.

issues.description: One or more connections for profile "Profile_2" are configured with Use-BIOS boot settings. OneView does not support profile connections configured with a mixture of Use-BIOS and other boot settings.
issues.recommendation: The Virtual Connect Use-BIOS boot setting will be automatically changed to "not bootable" when the profile is migrated to OneView. If this change is acceptable, proceed with the migration.

issues.description: The WWNs for FCoE connection 1 of profile "Profile_2" will change to "user-specified" to maintain connectivity and retain the currently assigned WWNs.
issues.recommendation: If this change is acceptable, proceed with the migration.

issues.description: The WWNs for FCoE connection 2 of profile "Profile_2" will change to "user-specified" to maintain connectivity and retain the currently assigned WWNs.
issues.recommendation: If this change is acceptable, proceed with the migration.
